          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Citizens' Right to Know Act of 2016</b></p> <p>This bill requires a state or local government that receives funds under a Department of Justice (DOJ) grant program and uses such funds for a pretrial services program to annually report certain information about participating defendants.</p> <p>DOJ must publish the information.</p> <p>Additionally, DOJ must reduce the grant allocation of a state or local government that fails to comply.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
